<td>Building blocks</td>
<td>Dirt or sand</td>
<td>1 ("half-door")
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>Work</td>
<td>Digs</td>
<td>6
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>Instead of a door, a single block of dirt is placed.
</p>
<dl><dd>You could wall yourself in completely, but then you wouldn't see when the night is over.</dd></dl>
<p>See also <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://wiki.minetest.net/Building_a_home#Cavehome_2">Cavehome2</a> below, 
how this might look when expanded to complete base/lair.
</p><p><br />
With flat terrain, and no hill or cliff, we also need some stairs to get down,<br />
e.g. underground shelter viewed from the side:
</p>
<table>

<tbody><tr>
<td>D</td>
<td>D</td>
<td>D</td>
<td>_</td>
<td>_</td>
<td>_
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>D</td>
<td>i</td>
<td>_</td>
<td>_</td>
<td>_</td>
<td>D
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>D</td>
<td>i</td>
<td>_</td>
<td>x</td>
<td>D</td>
<td>D
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>S</td>
