<p>W=wall/window  D=door  _=free space  ^=center - with protection-block, maybe ladder <br />
a,b=bed  c=chest  F=furnace t,h=table,chair <br />
s,#=stairs  P=platform/balcony  f=fence/glass-panes as handrail
</p><p>Stairs are running around one corner of the tower. <br />
On the next floor, it would continue (...) where the last stairs arrive. <br />
So, the stairs make one complete turn after every 4 floors. <br />
There is room below the stairs for 2 or 3 blocks, eg. chests and/or furnace.
</p><p>To make the stairs fit, Windows need to be 1 block high, rooms 3 high.
</p><p>...
</p>
<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Round_Tower_9x9">Round Tower 9x9</span></h4>
<p>A tower of size 7x7 with cut-off corners is the minimum to make it look somewhat 'round'.
</p><p>With 9x9, it will look more well-rounded:
</p>
